article.headline: Penn 73, Columbia 54
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Brian Grandieri scored 17 points, hitting all eight of his shots, and Ibrahim Jaaber had 15 points and seven assists as Penn defeated Columbia 73-54 Friday night. Mark Zoller added 14 points and Steve Danley had 11 for Penn (16-8, 7-1 Ivy), which hit 27 of 44 shots in the game, for 61.4 percent. Niko Scott had 14 points and Mack Montgomery made 11 for the Lions (13-10, 4-5), who have now lost nine of 10 games to the Quakers. Columbia trailed only 48-40 with 10:46 to play, but Zoller sparked a 9-2 Quaker run to give Penn a 57-42 advantage. A 3-point play by Jaaber boosted the margin to 65-48 at the 5:11 mark. Columbia had a 19-14 lead midway through the first half, before Penn went on a 17-2 spurt, with six players scoring, to lead 31-21.
